  "title": "Site Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>A Construction Civil Engineering organization established in 2013 by four established local A1 main contractors in Singapore. The company is currently engaged in civil LTA projects. It fosters a teamwork environment with a continuous learning mindset.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Join a leading main contractor for LTA projects as a Civil Engineer, driving site execution excellence through proactive project monitoring, technical oversight, and stakeholder coordination to deliver quality infrastructure within schedule and budget.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist Project Engineers on site to support project delivery and resolve technical issues promptly</li><li>Monitor site progress and schedule to ensure timely completion of project milestones</li><li>Manage site set out, leveling, and surveying activities to maintain construction accuracy</li><li>Review and verify plans, drawings, and quantity calculations to ensure compliance with design specifications</li><li>Ensure all materials and workmanship conform to project specifications and budget constraints</li><li>Supervise project crews and subcontractors to maintain productivity and quality standards</li><li>Coordinate effectively with authorities, clients, and Qualified Persons (QP) to facilitate approvals and compliance</li><li>Enforce safety, health, and security protocols within the assigned work area to maintain a safe working environment</li><li>Adapt to and perform efficiently in a fast-paced construction environment</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Civil Engineering recognized by the Professional Engineers Board</li><li>Minimum 2-3 years of civil engineering experience</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Ability to work effectively under fast-paced and dynamic site conditions</li></ul>",
